# Trivy IaC scan suppressions.
# Format: one check ID per line, with a comment justifying the suppression.

# KSV0024 (host ports): the opengate server Deployment publishes QUIC (9090/udp)
# and Intel AMT MPS (4433/tcp) via hostPort on the single OKE node — a deliberate
# L4 design decision (ADR-030 §5: budget-free, source-IP preserving). Restricted
# to those two known ports; the multi-node path moves them off hostPort.
KSV-0024

# Monitoring stack (deploy/helm/monitoring) — findings inherent to host-level
# exporters (ADR-030 §4). node-exporter must share the host PID namespace and
# mount host /proc /sys / to read node metrics; uptime-kuma (a Node app) writes
# beyond its data PVC so a read-only root filesystem is not feasible.
#
# KSV-0014 (readOnlyRootFilesystem) also covers the postgres StatefulSet — the
# official postgres image writes to several runtime paths beyond PGDATA.
KSV-0010   # node-exporter hostPID — required to read per-process node metrics
KSV-0121   # node-exporter hostPath /proc /sys / — required for node metrics
KSV-0014   # readOnlyRootFilesystem — uptime-kuma + postgres write beyond their volumes
